The paper deals with the relationship between information and estimation in the presence of Gaussian noise, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also explores the nature of pointwise relations between random quantities, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.MM) and statistics (cs.SI). The paper uses mathematical identities and explores the nature of random variables, which are topics that fall under theoretical computer science (cs.LG) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
